						               													<description>Komma Lika (Come Equally)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Every time you do something for the shared household &amp;ndash; the dishes, replace a broken light bulb, take the car to the auto shop, etc. &amp;ndash; you get points. The points consist of triangular shaped magnets of different sizes. Each member of the household gets his/her own color, and together the different colored magnets form a nice pattern. When the game period is finished, the colors should ideally be balanced and equally distributed. Everybody wins by getting equal.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It is up to you to decide how long you want the game period to be. A week or two, until you run out of magnets, or until you together have formed one of the figures shown on the cards that come with the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Try playing a first round while leading your lives as usual, collecting points according to the rules. Evaluate the results. Are the colors balanced? Play again &amp;ndash; this time, try to get as equal as possible.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Who wins? It&amp;rsquo;s not about winning &amp;ndash; it&amp;rsquo;s about getting equal.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
